Company Profile



The Siam Cement Public Co. Ltd. is an investment holding company. It engages in the business of industrial supplies and construction industries. The company operates through six segments: Chemicals, Paper, Cement, Building Materials, Distribution and Investment. The Chemicals segment manufactures and sells olefins, polyolefins and other chemical products. The Paper segment deals with the manufacture and sale of printing and writing paper, gypsum linerboard, industrial paper, corrugated boxes and securities document. The Cement segment consists of grey cement, ready-mixed concrete, white cement and dry mortar. The Building Materials segment deals with the manufacture and sale of roof tiles, concrete paving blocks, ceramic tiles, sanitary wares and sanitary fittings. The Distribution segment distributes and exports cement, steel, building and decorative products, fuel products, waste paper and scrap iron. The Investment segment invests with the companies in other businesses, such as agricultural machine, automotive parts and components and steel. The company was founded by King Rama VI on June 14, 1913 and is headquartered in Bangkok, Thailand.

























